    <projectName>PFunc</projectName>
    <projectDescription>
   PFunc, short for Parallel Functions, is a lightweight and
   portable library that provides C and C++ APIs to express
   task parallelism. The features offered by PFunc are a strict
   superset of the features offered by current solutions for
   task parallelism such as Cilk and Intel's Threading Building
   Blocks.  Specifically, PFunc extends the feature set of
   current solutions with custom task scheduling, task priorities
   and task affinities. Furthermore, PFunc offers task groups
   for SPMD-style programming and multiple task completion
   notifications for parallel execution of DAGs.  PFunc's
   extended feature set is geared towards helping knowledgeable
   users optimize their application performance.
    </projectDescription>
